<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AIR-TO-AIR CHARGE AIR COOLER - AIR LEAK TEST - LEAKAGE
        TESTER HOOK-UP
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="2">
        <title>LEAKAGE TESTER HOOK-UP</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Charge Air Cooler Inlet Connection (Turbocharger Exhaust "Hot" Side)</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para id="hl1200607">To prevent foreign matter from entering the engine, cover the turbocharger
                        exhaust and intake piping while the charge air cooler is disconnected.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the turbocharger exhaust piping (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200610">Figure 10</hotlnk>) from the charge air cooler hose (Item 5,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200610">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Refer to the ,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl1200607">CAUTION
                        <xref refid="hl1200607"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="f1200610" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1200610" filename="../figg12/G1200610.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Typical Charge Air System</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>A. TURBOCHARGER EXHAUST (HOT SIDE)</callout1>
                        <callout1>B. ENGINE AIR INTAKE (COLD SIDE)</callout1>
                        <callout1>1. HOT SIDE PIPE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. COLD SIDE PIPE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOSE CLAMP</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. COLD SIDE HOSE</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. HOT SIDE HOSE</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200611">Figure 11</hotlnk>for the following items in parentheses, unless otherwise
                    stated.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1200611" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1200611" filename="../figg12/G1200611.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Test Equipment Hook-Up</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. HOSE CLAMP</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. EXHAUST (HOT SIDE) HOSE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. INTAKE (COLD SIDE) HOSE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. GAUGE COUPLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SAFETY CHAIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. GAUGE-REGULATOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. QUICK DISCONNECT FITTING</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. BLEED-OFF COUPLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. QUICK DISCONNECT FITTING</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. AIR VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>11. AIR GAUGE</callout1>
                        <callout1>12. BLEED-OFF VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>13. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the gauge coupler (Item 4,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200611">Figure 11</hotlnk>) to the charge air cooler hose. Secure the coupler with
                    a clamp so it is AIR TIGHT. Tighten the clamp to the value in the
                    <hotlnk document="s12006_18.xml" xrefid="hl1200606">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl1200606"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the safety chain (Item 5) to any convenient capscrew on the radiator bracket.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>To prevent possible injury from the coupler blowing off the charge air cooler hose during
                            the test, CONNECT THE SAFETY CHAIN BEFORE APPLYING AIR PRESSURE.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the gauge-regulator assembly (Item 6) on the gauge coupler (Item 4) at the quick
                    disconnect fitting (Item 7) on the coupler.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Charge Air Cooler Outlet Connection (Engine Air Intake "Cold" Side)</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para id="hl1200608">To prevent foreign matter from entering the engine, cover the turbocharger
                        exhaust and intake piping while the charge air cooler is disconnected.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the engine air intake piping (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200610">Figure 10</hotlnk>
                    ) from the charge air cooler hose (Item 4 ). Refer to the
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl1200608">CAUTION
                        <xref refid="hl1200608"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200611">Figure 11</hotlnk>for the following items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the bleed-off coupler (Item 8) to the charge air cooler hose (Item 3). Secure
                    the coupler with a clamp so it is AIR TIGHT. Tighten the clamp to the value in the
                    <hotlnk document="s12006_18.xml" xrefid="hl1200606">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl1200606"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the safety chain (Item 5) to any convenient capscrew on the radiator.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>To prevent possible injury from the coupler blowing off the charge air cooler hose during
                            the test, CONNECT THE SAFETY CHAIN BEFORE APPLYING AIR PRESSURE.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
